<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT, CONNECTING
        RODS AND PISTONS - Crankcase Reconditioning - Inspect Short Circuit Valve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Inspect Short Circuit Valve</title>
        <figure id="f1200762" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/eg1894.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Short Circuit Components</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">O-Ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Plug</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Spring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Check Ball</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a hex head wrench to remove the plug located in the top left front of the crankcase.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the plug, O-ring, spring, and the check ball for wear. Also check the ball seat in
                the valve port of the crankcase. Replace any worn items.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the ball and spring into the valve port. Apply clean engine oil to the O-ring and
                place it onto the plug.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Screw the plug into the crankcase. Tighten the plug to the standard torque value.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
